---

## Key Takeaways

- Always check CMS versions ‚Äî Joomla 3.7.0 has a well-known critical SQLi
- Bcrypt is slow to crack but rockyou.txt will eventually find weak passwords
- Config files often contain reused credentials ‚Äî always check them
- GTFOBins is your friend: `yum` with sudo is a clean privesc path
- The RPM install approach for yum privesc can fail on older systems due to `rpmlib(LargeFiles)` compatibility ‚Äî the plugin method is more reliable and requires no file transfer
